2><strong>About Radiant</strong></h2><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Radiant =
is an El Segundo, CA-based startup building the world=E2=80=99s first mass-=
produced, portable nuclear microreactors. The company=E2=80=99s first react=
or, Kaleidos, is a 1-megawatt, fail-safe microreactor that can be transport=
ed anywhere power is needed and run for up to 5 years without refueling. Po=
rtable nuclear power with rapid-deploy capability can replace similar-sized=
 diesel generators and provide critical asset support for hospitals, data c=
enters, remote sites, and military bases. Radiant=E2=80=99s unique, practic=
al approach to nuclear development leverages modern software engineering to=
 rapidly deliver safe, factory-built microreactors that use existing, well-=
qualified materials. Founded in 2020, Radiant is on track to test its first=
 reactor at the Idaho National Laboratory this summer, with initial custome=
r deliveries beginning in 2028.</p><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em"></p><h2><s=
trong>About the Role</strong></h2><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Radiant is =
seeking a driven Principal Software Engineer to own on-site High-Performanc=
e Compute infrastructure, scientific computing environments, and automation=
 projects in tight collaboration with hard-science users and cloud infrastr=
ucture engineers. You will work closely with the software team to design sc=
alable, secure, and resilient compute practices, tools, and systems across =
the entire organization.</p><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">As a technical le=
ad, you will define team scope, shape individual responsibilities, and serv=
e as the primary liaison between engineering and software teams, acting as =
the subject-matter expert on HPC workflows, simulation tooling, and compute=
 optimization. The ideal candidate is patient, organized, and comfortable m=
anaging high volumes of cross-disciplinary requests, capable of diving deep=
 into complex legacy stacks and synthesizing findings. The infrastructure y=
ou manage, the pipelines you build, and the developer-productivity culture =
you establish will help you design, run, and mass-produce the first high-te=
mperature gas-cooled portable microreactor ever to be commercialized.</p><p=
 style=3D"min-height:1.5em"></p><h2><strong>Responsibilities &amp; Duties</=
strong></h2><ul style=3D"min-height:1.5em"><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em=
">Lead HPC initiatives as driven by the software org, establishing responsi=
bilities, project scope, and technical mentorship.</p></li><li><p style=3D"=
min-height:1.5em">Own workflows, tooling, and performance for scientific co=
mputing, including Ansys, STAR-CCM+, and Abaqus, covering licensing, enviro=
nment setup, job orchestration, and results infrastructure.</p></li><li><p =
style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Dive deep into HPC software, workload scheduling=
, data movement, storage hierarchies, and compute environments to build rob=
ust, high-throughput Linux systems.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5e=
m">Serve as the go-between for engineering teams and software, fielding HPC=
 questions, simulation software issues, and infrastructure needs from nucle=
ar, thermal, materials, mechanical, and electrical engineers, translating t=
hem into actionable work.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Triage =
inbound infrastructure requests, HPC/MPI/Linux debugging, job failure analy=
sis, and shell and systems mentorship, while prioritizing effectively and c=
ommunicating clearly across stakeholders.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-heigh=
t:1.5em">Modernize legacy scientific computing systems and tooling, migrati=
ng to current stacks to improve maintainability, performance, and developer=
 experience.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Design and maintain =
networking infrastructure for distributed simulation systems, optimizing da=
ta transfer between HPC clusters.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em"=
>Partner with DevOps engineers to architect and maintain systems across AWS=
 and on-premises Linux environments, ensuring high availability, security, =
and performance for mission-critical workloads.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min=
-height:1.5em">Architect tools supporting build systems, testing frameworks=
, deployment automation, and developer environments.</p></li></ul><p style=
=3D"min-height:1.5em"></p><h2><strong>Required Qualifications &amp; Skills<=
/strong></h2><ul style=3D"min-height:1.5em"><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5e=
m">Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Physics or a related=
 technical field.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">8+ years of pro=
fessional experience in HPC, scientific computing, infrastructure, or platf=
orm engineering.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Deep Linux and s=
ysadmin fluency, file systems, process management, and networking, with a h=
ard-science approach to problem-solving.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height=
:1.5em">Hands-on experience with HPC environments, simulation workloads, or=
 academic/research computing (SLURM, PBS, MPI, Lustre, EFS, AWS ParallelClu=
ster, or similar).</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Strong profici=
ency in one or more languages: Python, Golang, Rust, C#, or C/C++.</p></li>=
<li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Strong code review skills, including the =
ability to read stack traces and chase down dense rabbit holes in high-comp=
liance, legacy scientific software environments.</p></li><li><p style=3D"mi=
n-height:1.5em">Exceptional communication skills; organized and effective w=
hen fielding a high volume of questions and requests from engineering stake=
holders.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Ability to dive deep int=
o complex, nested legacy stacks and then zoom out to synthesize findings cl=
early for a broader technical audience.</p></li></ul><p style=3D"min-height=
:1.5em"></p><h2><strong>Desired Qualifications &amp; Skills</strong></h2><u=
l style=3D"min-height:1.5em"><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Master's deg=
ree or higher in Computer Science, Engineering, Physics, or a related techn=
ical field.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Hands-on physical inf=
rastructure experience: server hardware, rack configuration, data center op=
s, or high-throughput networking (InfiniBand, Slingshot, AWS EFA).</p></li>=
<li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Experience working cross-functionally wit=
h engineering teams across mechanical, electrical, materials, and nuclear d=
isciplines.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Working experience wi=
th Kubernetes and Docker for orchestration and deployment.</p></li><li><p s=
tyle=3D"min-height:1.5em">Cloud infrastructure experience with Ansible, Ter=
raform, or AWS in a cloud-native or hybrid environment.</p></li><li><p styl=
e=3D"min-height:1.5em">Experience with adjacent HPC domains, AI/ML training=
 infrastructure, edge computing, quantum computing, visual computing (rende=
r farms), or big data analytics, where distributed hardware, GPU accelerati=
on, and large-scale compute requirements overlap with traditional HPC envir=
onments.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Comfortable picking up f=
rontend work when needed, React or general JavaScript experience is a plus;=
 an open mind toward full-stack contributions is more important than depth =
here.</p></li></ul><div style=3D"min-height:1.2em;margin-top:0;margin-botto=
m:0">&nbsp;</div><h2><strong>Additional Requirements:</strong></h2><ul styl=
e=3D"min-height:1.5em"><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Must be willing to=
 work extended hours and weekends as necessary to accomplish our mission.</=
p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Must work 100% onsite at El Segund=
o HQ.</p><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em"></p></li></ul><h1><strong>Benefits a=
nd Perks</strong></h1><ul style=3D"min-height:1.5em"><li><p style=3D"min-he=
ight:1.5em">Stock: Substantial incentive stock plan for all full-time emplo=
yees.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Medical: 100% up to base si=
lver level plan for employee + 50% dependents, offers up to Platinum plans.=
</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">One Medical: Sponsored membershi=
ps for employees and their dependents.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1=
.5em">Vision: 100% top tier plan coverage + 50% for dependents.</p></li><li=
><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Dental: 100% top tier plan coverage, orthodo=
ntia extra, 50% for dependents.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">V=
oluntary life, accident, hospital, critical illness, commuter and FSA/HSA a=
re offered as employee contributed benefits.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-he=
ight:1.5em">8-weeks of paid parental leave for all parents. Additional paid=
 pregnancy leave for CA employees.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em=
">Daily catered lunch. Free snacks and drinks.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-=
height:1.5em">Flexible PTO policy. Remote workday allocation.</p></li><li><=
p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Company and team-bonding events, happy hours a=
nd in-person camaraderie.</p></li><li><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em">Beautif=
ul El Segundo headquarters close to the Pacific Ocean.</p></li></ul><p styl=
e=3D"min-height:1.5em"></p><p style=3D"min-height:1.5em"><strong>Total Comp=
ensation and Benefits</strong><br>Radiant compensates people for impact and=
 invests in those who continue to raise the bar. Radiant=E2=80=99s new hire=
 compensation package includes base salary, substantial equity grants, and =
comprehensive health benefits. Total compensation and level are determined =
through a rigorous evaluation of interview performance, experience, educati=
on, and qualifications, and are designed to support continued growth as sco=
pe, responsibility, and impact expand at Radiant.<br><br>The best of today=
=E2=80=99s advanced reactor builders don=E2=80=99t wait for job postings. T=
hey join the winning team. If that=E2=80=99s you, contact us directly for i=
mmediate opportunities: <a target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener" href=3D"mailt=
o:recruiting@radiantnuclear.com">recruiting@radiantnuclear.com</a>.<br><br>=
<em>We are an equal opportunity employer and all qualified applicants will =
receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religio=
n, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, pregnancy, age, =
national origin, disability status, genetic information, protected veteran =
status, or any other characteristic protected by law.</em></p><p style=3D"m=
in-height:1.5em"><em>This position involves access to technology that is su=
bject to U.S. export controls. Any job offer made will be contingent upon t=
he applicant=E2=80=99s capacity to serve in compliance with U.S. export con=
trols.</em></p><p style=3D"display: none;">Compensation Range: $200,500 - $=
